base64
- converts any text or code to binary code (just text conversion)
• base64 normal.txt > coded.txt 
   *if we cat coded.txt , we get a jumbled code
base64 coded.txt > decoded.txt
    *if we cat decided.txt , we get original text
• base64 ends with =, only A-Z a-z 0-9 + /

rot13 and ciphers
• ROT13 / Caesar - Alphabetic but nonsense (their pattern)

rot13
- it's just cipher with shift of 13 digits 
   i.e. A +13 = N
   cat coded.txt | tr 'A-Za-z' 'N-ZA-Mn-za-m' > decoded.txt
  • now if we cat decoded.txt , we can see the secret text
• To convert any text to rot13 then use
echo 'your text here' | tr 'A-Za-z' 'N-ZA-Mn-za-m'

Caesar cipher
- it's just any random shift 
we use cipher brute force to check all 26 alphabets (26 possible shifts) and decode it
• first we convert alphabet to numbers then add a number(shift) to all those numbers and we get new number, convert that new number to alphabet 
and donee
• for i in {1..26}; do echo "$i:"; cat coded.txt | tr "A-Za-z" "$(echo {A..Z} {a..z} | tr -d ' ' | cut -c $((i+1))-)$(echo {A..Z} {a..z} | tr -d ' ' | cut -c 1-$i)"; echo; done

Vigenère cipher
- advanced caesar cipher, it shifts based on the key
Example: HELLO - text
                 KEYKE - key
      First letter: H(7) + K(10) = 17 (R)
      So on....
• we don't use linux terminal to decode this instead we use online decider for vigenère cipher and give both code and key, it will automatically give us decoded code
• manual formula 
   *first convert alphabet to numbers 
   *then apply formula
   *output will be in numbers
   *again convert numbers to text
   Plain = (Cipher - Key + 26) mod26
  [ A=0,B=1,.....,Z=26 ]

hex
• Hex only 0-9 + a-f, pairs like 68 65 6c 6c 6
- decode hex
echo "626173653634" | xxd -r -p

mod26
- it is the math behind all those cipher problems

See first we take the code ciphers (which are in alphabets) and convert them into numbers [ A=0,..., Z=26]

Eg: now suppose W(22) , we have shift 5 then 
 W + 5 = 27 

Here we have two methods 
(1)  A  B          Y  Z
       0  1          25 26
       again loop
       27 28       (27+25)  (27+26)
This is not best soln so we use 2nd method

(2) 27 mod26 [ mod means remainder]
      27 % 26 = 1
And 1 = B
So W + 5 = B

Interencdec
- it is the jumbled code where there are multiple code one inside another
base64 -> hex -> rot13 -> plain text

PicoCTF is the place where we can practise all these

Linux luminarium is how to decode all of these using Linux terminal
